28/08/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- President Boris Tadic and UN High Commissioner for Refugees Antonio Guterres agreed on Thursday (August 27th) that the unresolved state of the refugee issue -- 17 years after the outbreak of conflicts in the Balkans -- is unacceptable. Guterres expressed satisfaction with efforts by Serbian authorities to help refugees from Croatia, support displaced people from Kosovo and help the Roma community. Tadic, in turn, pointed out that resolving the refugee problem is crucial to final reconciliation among all nations in the Balkans.
In other news, Foreign Minister Vuk Jeremic travels to New York on Friday for talks with officials from the UN secretary-general's office. He will meet with the permanent representatives to the UN of Azerbaijan, Vietnam, Nigeria, Brazil and other countries. (RTS, Tanjug, Beta, B92, Radio Srbija - 27/08/09)
